      "Community allowed to leave muster but not return to work"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 21, 2023, at 0930 hours, the Variable Frequency Device A (VFD-A) failed at the Perdido Spar platform in Alaminos Canyon Block 857, releasing smoke and activating smoke detectors in the Subsea Motor Control Center room. The failure was caused by the B-phase reactor on the VFD-A failing to ground, resulting in smoke generation. The automated facility shut-in system functioned as designed, triggering personnel muster. Cabinet A reached 350\u00b0F while other cabinets reached 210\u00b0F. No injuries or pollution were reported. The estimated replacement cost was $65,000.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Siemens to investigate why the reactor thermal switch did not trip the drive on over temperature"
    ],
